      <description>1984. Minimum Difference Between Highest and Lowest of K Scores #  Problem #  You are given a 0-indexed integer array nums, where nums[i] represents the score of the ith student. You are also given an integer k.
Pick the scores of any k students from the array so that the difference between the highest and the lowest of the k scores is minimized.
Return the minimum possible difference.</description>
